Checking if a CPU Feature called PCID is available on the linux kernel:
cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep pcid

The feature is only available in 64-bit x86 and the kernel needs to be built with it enabled. We recommend checking your environment to ensure that itâ€™s enabled, you can do this by running cat /proc/cpuinfo | grep pcid.
