MOZILLA FIREFOX TIPS

	USING AND MANAGING DIFFERENT PROFILES ON MOZILLA
		This might come in handy if you like using RamDisk:
			$ firefox -P

		Note: Profiles are located under  ~/.mozilla/ 

	MOZILLA FIREFOX HOTKEYS

	ctrl + shift + n	#Restores Previously Closed Tabs if you have at least 1 window open
	F7			#Enables Caret Mode: Allows cursor to be set on text when clicked 
				 ENABLING CARET MODE IN FIREFOX

	alt+<numbers>		#Changes tab
	ctrl + mouse_click	#Opens link in new tab
	ctrl + shift + s	#Built-in screenshot tool


	RESTORING MOZILLA SESSION
		Aside from using 'ctrl + shift + t', it's also possible to restore lost mozilla sessions by
		retrieving the backup files, this method is the best one since the prior requires you to remember
		which tabs you had open:

		1) Shutdown Firefox

		2) Default Location for Mozilla Profiles:
			 ~/.mozilla/firefox

		3) By launching firefox using the following argument 'firefox -P' from the commandline,
		it's possible to fetch the name of the current default profile as well as other profiles.

		4) From commandline, change directory to your mozilla profile:
			$ cd ~/.mozilla/firefox/xky2do8r.default-release

		5) Backup your mozilla session store directory:
			$ cp -ar ./sessionstore-backup ./sessionstore-backup-1

		6) (Optional) Just in case, backup your current session:
			$ cp -ar ./sessionstorage.jsonlz4 ./sessionstorage.jsonlz4-1

		7) Listing available sessions:
			$ ls -lh ./sessionstore-backup-1

		8) Restoring a previous session by picking up one of the '.jsonlz4' files:
			$ cp -ar ./sessionstore-backup-1/upgrade.jsonlz4-2025080716105 ./sessionstorage.jsonlz4

		9) Launch Firefox

