---SOME THUNDERBIRD MAIL CLIENT STUFF

	COPYING AND PASTING ALL SENDERS/DESTINATION FROM MAIL
		1 - Open the mail you want to copy senders/destination from >> ..
			.. >> Click on 'MORE' options, right by 'DELETE' >> ..
			.. >> Click on 'View Source' >> ..
			.. >> Copy Mail sender/destination right from source using CTRL+C

		2 - You can now paste with CTRL+V anywhere

	PARAGRAPH LINE BREAK
		By default, thunderbird uses line-break to insert new paragraphs when creating/edit mails or drafts.
		Instead of changing the default configuration, use 'CTRL + ENTER_KEY' to insert a new line without 
		breaking it into a new paragraph.
	
	PASSWORD AND IDENTIFICATION SETTINGS
		Specially when using OAUTH2, it's important to make sure each email is configured and set to OAUTH2.
	
		1 - Click on 'Settings' (it's right by the Cog Icon) >> ..
			.. >> Click on 'Privacy and Security' >> ..
			.. >> Saved Passwords >> ..
	
		USING PRIMARY PASSWORD FOR THUNDERBIRD
			An access password can be set for 'thunderbird' on the same section.

		
	SETTING UP THUNDERBIRD MAIL CLIENT ON ANDROID
		After adding an account, go to settings by clicking on the 'clog' icon,
	then select the email account, click on the 'Fetching mail' option, 
	click on 'Incoming Server' and finally setup the incoming server settings, then click 'next'.
	
