	HOW TO KILL A FROZEN APPLICATION UNDER WINDOWS 11
		If you can minimize the application, you can simply use 'system_key + d' then skip to step #3.
	'ctrl + alt + del' might not work at all if the frozen program takes over the full screen,
	on that case you'll have to follow instructions from step #1.

		1) Press shift + tab
		2) Move the frozen application to a new desktop
		3) Now select the free desktop and press ctrl + alt + del
			3.1) Click on 'Task Manager'
			3.2) Right click the application inside the task manager and kill it

	INSTALLING WINDOWS WITHOUT A HOTMAIL OR MICROSOFT ACCOUNT
