FIXING GPG: WARNING: UNSAFE PERMISSIONS ON HOMEDIR '/HOME/PATH/TO/USER/.GNUPG' 

Run this script:
#!/usr/bin/env bash

1) Make a backup to make sure you can revert the process in case something goes terribly wrong:
	$ cp -ar ~/.gnupg/ ~/.gnupg-backup

2) Make sure that the .gnupg directory and its contents is accessibile by your user.
	$ chown -R $(whoami) ~/.gnupg/

3) Correct permissions and access on the directory:
	$ chmod 600 ~/.gnupg/*
	$ chmod 700 ~/.gnupg

